task.summary: Default task
Wild goose chase going on on but fixing bugs left and right.
Little more cleanup and bug fixes. Everything is working as expected

Made the global allocator lockable by putting higher order locked wrapper functions in. Appears to work. The old functions can just be used lockless for the nested dependencies that can arise when data structures need to be dynamically allocated during an allocation. All regular allocations must now use kmalloc.
Removing the commented out code in tempfs_init. I ran a test allocating most of the pages in the system to ensure that the allocator can handle a beating and it can.
Extensive logic bug fixes. Things are looking very good now. Just need to handle the newly discovered null slab issue but not top priority as aborting works fine for now.
Moved the bug message into heap_free_in_slab
Appear to have fixed more fundamental issues in the singly_linked_list.c and bst functions and am now back to debugging what is going on in tempfs.c
Put a bandaid solution in for the bad slab addresses will address it later

Messing around with slab allocator. Can't figure out why the occasional bad free is happening. It doesn't seem to happen too much so it might be okay to leave as is but I may rewrite the slab allocator.
Fixed the slab allocator , the mask on free was set for 1 page not 64
Fixed the allocation issues in tempfs.c for second and third level indirection blocks
debugging indirection allocation. Something wonky going on.
fixed single indirect allocation now onto double and triple
Fixed double indirect allocation.
Fixed final issue with double indirect allocation. Can successfully write 600,000 byte files and edit any portion of the file etc and it works. Feels good.
More stress testing and finding breaking components in the list functions going back to those.

Found the cause of the current bug. The way to indntify a slab was just checking if the address started on a page boundary, this wont work anymore. Going to use a hash table to store slab addresses and check that way.

Fucking fixed it, thank christ. Now slab deallocs work properly given the new 64 page slab size. Ripped the hash table out because it's unecessary for the number of slabs we have. If I ever have an obscene amount of slabs then I can think about a hash table.
Testing is almost at a point where we can move on. Testing file deletion. Freeing bitmap isnt working it appears so debugging that.
Fixed bitmap free issue. Almost all tempfs functions are ready to go.
Fixed the get dir entries function it is testing properly now.
in tempfs_create
more testing and minor fixes in block_free function
Fixed block allocation scheme in tempfs_write_dirent. It wouldnt deallocate on an empty dir and keep allocating if you delete an entry and add a new one.
onto testing recursive directory freeing and the like
Fixed tempfs_create returning a null vnode
Fixed get_inode_and_mark_bitmap function it was incrementing by block not byte
Fixed directory freeing now frees blocks and inodes correctly.
tempfs_lookup now works properly and fills the vnode children properly.
Removed testing code in tempfs_mkfs and removed redundant unsafe free in vnode_free
const identifiers where needed in tempfs.c
some changes going to set up the file handle table in the process structure and have a list of them.
tempfs open and close , having a bitmap for handle ids
Starting to flesh out more vfs functionality
fleshing out more vfs functionality
finished vnode close for now, need to implement the remove node by addr function in doubly_linked_list.c
still some work to do with vfs but starting to set up the kthread functionality since it will be used to test the vfs
Added clang-tidy file and fixed import. IDE is still fucked so gonna try reimporting project yet again.
Some PCI scratch to be built and fixed as I go
Decices are only being added to list if they are a recognizable type
Proper Device scanning being done and adding most of the fields (not all)
pci_read_config was whacked, now fixed I believe
morning brain had me write that bunch of redundant nonsense so I removed it lol
Got rid of dynamic allocation for pci devs

Added pci driver abstraction struct with function pointers, fixed stack free bug in free_process and created a new process field in the process(in the process of changing the process field) . That's a lot of the word process.
removed all the explicit type defs in kalloc and slab since it's not my personal style and I want to be consistent
Laying out device.h among other things.
